<subSubSection id="C32E65595C81FF2548A6F97DFB28F84A" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25C81FF2548A6F97DFB28F84A" blockId="158.[151,1437,1014,1975]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C81FF2548A6F97DFEF5F946" bold="true" box="[199,315,1698,1723]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C81FF254AF0F97CFCD4F946" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[657,794,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olivaceus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C81FF254AF0F97CFCD4F946" box="[657,794,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">A. olivaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body black; the clypeus rounded and short; the antennal scrobe carinate; the eye small; the notaulus wide; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea and mesopleural suture closed; the paramere distinctly longer than the basiparamere; the basivolsella with an inner marginal excavation; the cuspis ventral arm with a basal projection; and the apical portion of the aedeagus wide, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C81FF254898F8ECFE4FF8B6" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[249,385,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olivaceus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C81FF254898F8ECFE4FF8B6" box="[249,385,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">A. olivaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body with darkish green reflection and the propodeum black; the clypeus angulate and long; the antennal scrobe carinate, but weak; the eye large; the notaulus very narrow; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea and mesopleural suture opened; the paramere longer than the basiparamere; the basivolsella straight; the cuspis ventral arm without a basal projection; and the aedeagus with the apical portion slender.
</paragraph>
